# Native media & uploads

## Convex uploads — modern File API only

- Use `uploadBinaryToConvex` from `@/lib/journal/upload-binary`.
- **Never** use `expo-file-system/legacy` `uploadAsync` — it fails on Android cache URIs (picked images, expo-audio recordings).

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
import { uploadAsync } from "expo-file-system/legacy";

// ✅ GOOD
import { uploadBinaryToConvex } from "@/lib/journal/upload-binary";
return uploadBinaryToConvex({ uri, mimeType, generateUploadUrl });
```

## expo-audio player source

Memoize the source object passed to `useAudioPlayer` — new `{ uri }` every render can recreate the player:

```tsx
const audioUri = value?.uri;
const playerSource = useMemo(
  () => (audioUri ? { uri: audioUri } : null),
  [audioUri],
);
const player = useAudioPlayer(playerSource);
```

## Audio mode setup

Do not swallow `setAudioModeAsync` errors with empty `.catch(() => {})`:

```tsx
.catch((err) => {
  console.warn("[ComponentName] setAudioModeAsync failed:", err);
});
```

## Duration / time math — zero is valid

Use nullish coalescing (`??`), not `||`, for `duration` and `currentTime`. `0` is falsy with `||`.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — treats 0 as missing
const duration = status.duration || 0;
Math.min(current, duration || Number.POSITIVE_INFINITY);

// ✅ GOOD
const duration = status.duration ?? 0;
Math.min(current, duration > 0 ? duration : Number.POSITIVE_INFINITY);
```
